Usage: sh makepBAM.sh <bam> <ref>

input: <bam> is the bam file that you want to process
       <ref>is the reference genome fasta

output: <bam_prefix>.p.bam, a p.bam file that has the same name as the bam before the extension. For example if bam filenam is FOO.bam, then the corresponding p.pam filename is FOO.p.bam.
